                       Statistical Policy and Research
     __________________________________________________________________

     Statistical Guidelines and Standards
     * BTS's Guide to Good Statistical Practice - DRAFT
     * Standards for Discussion and Presentation of Errors in Survey and
       Census Data - Published by the Journal of the American Statistical
       Association in 1975, this document is based on Technical Paper 32
       issued by the U.S. Census Bureau in 1974 (in Adobe Acrobat format)
     * The Energy Information Administration's Standards Manual
     * Statistics Canada Quality Guidelines

     Statistical Consulting on GPRA

     BTS has consulted with the Operating Administrations within DOT on
     their performance measures in the DOT 2001 Performance Plan and 1999
     Report. One result of this work is the compendium of Source and
     Accuracy Statements for each of the data programs used to create
     performance measurements.
     * Source & Accuracy Compendium

     Economic Classification
     * S.I.C. Pursuits: The Consequences and Problems of Classifying
       Establishments for Government Statistics (1987)
     * North American Industrial Classification System (NAICS)
     * Commodity Classification

     Data Collection and Tabulation Geography
     * National Transportation Analysis Regions (NTARs)

     Statistical Methods Research by BTS
     * Counting the New Mobile Workforce, a report in Adobe Acrobat format
       on methods for surveying home-based work.
     * Implications of Continuous Measurement for the Uses of Census Data
       in Transportation Planning, a printed report concerning the
       decennial census that can be ordered by email.

     Federal Committee on Statistical Methodology (FCSM)
     * Purpose and Activities of the FCSM
     * Statistical Policy Working Papers of the FCSM and Related
       Methodology Reports


